# Permissions Lab

## Commands Used
- ls -l
- chmod
- chown

## Key Learnings
- Linux uses rwx permissions
- Permissions are divided into owner, group, others
- chmod changes access rights
- chown changes ownership
- 600 = private file
- 644 = standard file
- 777 = full access (not secure)
